        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have heard from the Treasury, &amp; they will pay you the account as soon as you like<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Chas Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> June 6<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</p>
<p>12 Upper Gower S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">There are annotations at the top of the letter probably made by Folthorp: N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. 7– 57 . 16 . 11 8– 51 . 16 . 2 ———— 109 . 13 . 1 These refer to the accounts rendered by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>. for the two most recent numbers of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8579.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Zoology</hi></ref>; the expenses for No. 7 (<hi rend="italic">Fossil Mammalia,</hi> No. 2) and for No. 8 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2623.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Fossil Mammalia</hi></ref>, No. 3). See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-512A.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to A. Y. Spearman, 27 May 1839</ref>, n. 1. At the foot of the page, in the same hand: <quote> Qy Smiths N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 5. 52 . 15 .</quote> This probably refers to a query about number 5 of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4396.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Andrew Smith’s</ref> <hi rend="italic">Illustrations of the zoology of South Africa,</hi> also published by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>. with a grant from the Treasury.</note>
